<HEADLINE>
Blair government welcomes 'very positive' IRA statement
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
LONDON, July 28
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A spokesman for British Prime Minister 
Tony Blair welcomed Thursday what he called a "very positive" 
statement from the Irish Republican Army leadership to end its armed 
campaign in Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman welcomed the IRA leadership's clear call to "end" 
the armed campaign and renounce "any other activities whatsoever," 
which he interpreted as an end to criminal activities.
</P>
<P>
The second phrase "is very important," the spokesman told AFP.
</P>
<P>
Overall the statement "is very positive," he added.
</P>
